craft /krɑːft/

(crafting,crafted,crafts) 

1. N-COUNT You can refer to a boat, a spacecraft, or an aircraft as a craft . 船; 航天器; 航空器 

例： With great difficulty, the fisherman manoeuvred his small craft close to the reef. 渔夫艰难地驾着小船靠近了礁石。 

2. N-COUNT A craft is an activity such as weaving, carving, or pottery that involves making things skilfully with your hands. 工艺 

例： ...the arts and crafts of the North American Indians. …北美印第安人的美术工艺。 

3. N-COUNT You can use craft to refer to any activity or job that involves doing something skilfully. 职业 

例： ...the craft of writing. …写作工作。 

4. V-T If something is crafted , it is made skilfully. 精心制作 [usu passive] 

例： The windows would probably have been crafted in the latter part of the Middle Ages. 这些窗户可能是中世纪后期精制而成。 

例： ...original, hand-crafted bags at affordable prices. …价格适中的独创手工包。

